tip.text: To be fair, they didn't say that they made their own bread, sausages or sauces, but if you're going to charge 180baht for the Danish dog, then you better have a damn good reason why. Poor effort.
The city reveals itself at every turn in this hotel but somehow you feel so removed from it all. Great breakfast spread, light and airy rooms, but the best part of this hotel has got to be the pool.
Jones the grocer and wild honey were closed.
The broth has probably been simmering in the giant cauldron since they've opened. So much flavour in the soup. Beef balls, parts of beef tip off this delicious bowl of beef noodle soup.
